  "texts": [
    "The first two types of approaches struggle with semantic understanding, limiting their ability to detect implicit toxicity.",
    "While methods of the third type can capture more complex semantics, their reliance on domain-specific training data results in significant performance degradation on out-of-domain data.",
    "However, due to their lightweight nature and ease of training, they are widely applied.",
    "The rapid development of large language models (LLMs) has provided new insights into the detection of toxic contents.",
    "Therefore, we try to explore whether LLM-based methods can outperform small models in this domain."
  ],
